    <title>Historic Downtown Preservation and Access Act</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-10-06T18:01:37Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Historic Downtown Preservation and Access Act </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow refundable tax credits for 50% of the expenses paid or incurred by the taxpayer during the year for: (1) installing an elevator or a sprinkler system in a certified historic structure, and (2) hazardous substance (lead paint, radon, and asbestos) abatement services with respect to a certified historic structure. The amount of each of the two credits, with respect to any taxpayer, may not exceed $50,000 per year. </p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <actionDate>2017-06-07</actionDate>
